9
00:00:48,420 --> 00:00:53,620
For example, sub-brown dwarfs, gas giants that form from collapsing gas clouds and the

10
00:00:53,620 --> 00:00:56,140
boring little brothers of brown dwarfs.

11
00:00:56,140 --> 00:01:00,900
They're a sort of failed star, and we'll now stop talking about them.

12
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:05,980
A far more interesting sort of rogue are terrestrial planets similar to Earth that got kicked out

13
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:07,900
of their planetary system.

14
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:13,020
Young star systems are dangerous places where protoplanets are battling for the available

15
