18
00:01:22,140 --> 00:01:26,900
If a very massive planet moves its orbit closer to the star, it can kick smaller planets

19
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:28,500
out of the system.

20
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:33,260
But just because a planet has survived the growing pains of formation doesn't mean it's

21
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:34,260
safe.

22
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:39,560
Planetary systems can be disrupted by flybys from stars or black holes at any point.

23
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:43,940
